The yen strengthened, erasing
earlier declines against the  U.S. dollar , after Japanese Finance
Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  announced a $100 billion effort to curb
gains in the national currency.  The yen traded at 76.70 per dollar as of 11:38 a.m. in
 Tokyo , from 76.66 yesterday in  New York , after earlier decling
to as weak as 76.87.  Japan â€™s currency advanced to 110.56 per
